snippet.textDisplay:
Oh wow. What an amazing melody, what masterful use of props and instruments. I'm a Punjabi Brit, but did I miss the translation ? Perhaps, but the masti, the energy, the sweetness, the stunning vocals esp of the chorus and the crescendos towards the end.... 
Is it a song, a prayer, a sentiment, I think all combined.
Going to play it aloud in my car. 
Rocking Bangla Sufi Jingle....

snippet.textDisplay:
Was Perplexed at the "megh de, paani de, chaya dede" almost said out loud that oh I understand Bengali...😂
Read in the comments that it was probably Rajasthani... That is why it was probably more understandable for someone like me from the mountains of lower KP, the opposite end of sub-continent.
But I feel if I listen very very carefully and allow some 'o' sounds I can pick up some words in Bengali. Probably because of familiarity with urdu and hindi. Am I right?

It seemed like a prayer of a song, references to Allah, and moulana. Of course I didn't click the subtitles.
Lovely work team CS Bangla.
Duas and best wishes from Pakistan.
